   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Early Intervention on Alcohol and Drug Abuse in SA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Substance abuse is a challenge in South Africa with detrimental effects on health, wealth and security of the nation. In South Africa drug abuse has been associated with crime, interpersonal violence, risky sexual behaviour (with accompanied increased risk of HIV acquisition and STI incidences), negative health of users and negative psychological impact to their families. Swahili Language Board of Southern Africa aim to combat alcohol and drug abuse amongst the young people in Western Cape.</narrative>
  </description>
